<TITLE> Indian envoy, wife escape injury in road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, April 7 (bdnews24.com)  Indian high commissioner Pinak R Chakravarty and his wife Radha Chakravarty had a lucky escape when a bus collided with their vehicle in Savar Monday afternoon. Police seized the bus and arrested the driver Quamruzzaman. Subinspector Shahin Parvez of Ashulia Police Station told bdnews24.com the accident occurred shortly before 2.30pm when a Manjil Paribahan bus was trying to overtake another vehicle near Nishchintapur Bus Stand. The front of the private car was partly damaged, though no one was seriously hurt. The Indian envoy and his wife were returning to Dhaka from Dinajpur. They later travelled back to the capital in the car of the high commission's protocol officer Binod Kumar. bdnews2
